{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2705","heading":"Delayed notice","label":"2705 Delayed notice","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptI/ch121","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs2705","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Effective DateSection effective 90 days after , and, in the case of conduct pursuant to a court order or extension, applicable only with respect to court orders or extensions made after such effective date, see , set out as a note under .Oct. 21, 1986section 202 of Pub. L. 99–508section 2701 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Delay of Notification","label":"a .—Delay of Notification","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs2705%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs2705%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs2705%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"where a court order is sought, include in the application a request, which the court shall grant, for an order delaying the notification required under for a period not to exceed ninety days, if the court determines that there is reason to believe that notification of the existence of the court order may have an adverse result described in paragraph (2) of this subsection; orsection 2703(b) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs2705%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"where an administrative subpoena authorized by a Federal or State statute or a Federal or State grand jury subpoena is obtained, delay the notification required under for a period not to exceed ninety days upon the execution of a written certification of a supervisory official that there is reason to believe that notification of the existence of the subpoena may have an adverse result described in paragraph (2) of this subsection.section 2703(b) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs2705%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft18%2Fs2705%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"endangering the life or physical safety of an individual;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t18/s2705/a/2","